<subSubSection id="4D3320B3556E085DB96B897065B45504" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="DB2EB76AFD9F403FE1706FE2C5D376DB" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ECCA64388AE3CC1416D12EFE001E713D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Like 
<taxonomicName id="42C9EBD47B73F2C0034F4960194A5DE3" genus="S." lsidName="S. dunalianum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="dunalianum">
<emphasis id="C3878A35011FB78EFDD0180DDF8E8BFF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. dunalianum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gaudich. but with narrowly elliptic to lanceolate leaves, many-branched inflorescences arising from the middle of the internode, and smaller fruits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
