and 
<taxonomicName id="81AA4E5DF5B0D62BDEF382CFDBE9C045" genus="S." lsidName="S. peekelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="peekelii">
<emphasis id="489298F7FF2E301C8B8C51C1EA7C020A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. peekelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2D2612E1FCCE1EA241EC413B13D29685" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="phenology">
<paragraph id="25F468E4D61D1DB5102981E5F3BDFC91" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Phenology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="41843994641BC8F90E6C62A14DAA8F13" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Known to flower and fruit in Apr. Perhaps fertile year round like the other members of 
<taxonomicName id="46353CF127E5FB943078A538327C3529" authority="Dunaliana" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum subsp. section" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Dunaliana" species="peekelii" subSpecies="section">Solanum section Dunaliana</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="81A7DF96110A68767F1ACF2A5D5B9FCA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="FBD95203575D144C295326D00379F034" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A51D14888108B72DEFDDF423DC2F1BD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The specific epithet was chosen to reflect the taxonomic labyrinth involving two other species of New Guinea 
<taxonomicName id="2B53E21E510ED07CB53A707418A72118" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E55790CA9AD4351D4225A10F929FC5B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that was unintentionally created by 
<bibRefCitation id="89B10C502FE0305F8EDE424B374BB1F2" author="Symon, DE" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Adelaide Botanic Gardens" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 171" refId="B25" refString="Symon, DE, 1985. The Solanaceae of New Guinea. Journal of the Adelaide Botanic Gardens 8: 1 - 171" title="The Solanaceae of New Guinea." volume="8" year="1985">Symon (1985)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="65A673C6262DAECADE915799CC6EE4DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="preliminary conservation assessment">
<paragraph id="E5E53C3DFFB0A37144063A99F78B6D00" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Preliminary conservation assessment</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AB6609EC95A16BCC961149F109A7D9B1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
(
<bibRefCitation id="0948BD9D3ECED7EC0D00B2709C9D8FB9" author="IUCN" journalOrPublisher="In: Aubreville A, Leroy J (Eds) Flore de La Nouvelle Caledonie et Dependances" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B13" refString="IUCN, 2019. Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee. http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" title="Guidelines for using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee." url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2019">IUCN 2019</bibRefCitation>
). EOO = 51 km2 [CR - Critically Endangered]; AOO = 12 km2 [EN - Endangered]. We assess 
<taxonomicName id="95B8979F9077725959EA2D4B0FF893D2" authorityName="D. McClelland" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum labyrinthinum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="labyrinthinum">
<emphasis id="F024F8C36AD62CBA853520A684F047E9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum labyrinthinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as EN (Endangered) using IUCN Criteria B1a,b, due to its restricted distribution, its primary forest habitat and lack of recent collections indicating population decline. Although it is found both on New Guinea and in the Solomon Islands, the destruction of lowland forest habitat in coastal areas suggests conservation concern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FE3DDCCFC3B5E4694E1E9E1DCFA87A0A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C1AE354FBCC92BE93E7F287324ED4C58" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Discussion.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1B3B3D04E7949C2C06F426362505F1BE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="ADA5732D44BE0E743A2CAA29372F1097" authorityName="D. McClelland" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum labyrinthinum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="labyrinthinum">
<emphasis id="0034A3746CDF78A9F962A71BD6A9EF4D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum labyrinthinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from other members of section 
<taxonomicName id="9CA89B8545E98539F897AAFB5F08ACDF" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Dunaliana">Dunaliana</taxonomicName>
(sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="51F7FC2536FA3C26DEC3A0212E265DAE" author="McClelland, DHR" journalOrPublisher="Trends in Ecology &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B16" refString="McClelland, DHR, 2012. Systematics and taxonomy of Solanum sections Dunaliana and Irenosolanum (Solanaceae). Doctoral dissertation presented to the City University of New York, NY." title="Systematics and taxonomy of Solanum sections Dunaliana and Irenosolanum (Solanaceae). Doctoral dissertation presented to the City University of New York, NY." year="2012">McClelland 2012</bibRefCitation>
) in its almost completely glabrous narrowly elliptic or somewhat lanceolate leaves. Like 
<taxonomicName id="E932EFBDD224E81D43D9B2BE52FF87C3" authorityName="Bitter" authorityYear="1917" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum torricellense" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="torricellense">
<emphasis id="18BA49E5CA81EDFEE80B5B5FFC7133B8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum torricellense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Bitter of New Guinea, but unlike the other members of this group (section 
<taxonomicName id="11C9CD8192A50982B856B8BE4F50D131" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Dunaliana">Dunaliana</taxonomicName>
sensu 
<bibRefCitation id="811430564D720991AE836649367FAFC0" author="McClelland, DHR" journalOrPublisher="Trends in Ecology &amp; Evolution" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" refId="B16" refString="McClelland, DHR, 2012. Systematics and taxonomy of Solanum sections Dunaliana and Irenosolanum (Solanaceae). Doctoral dissertation presented to the City University of New York, NY." title="Systematics and taxonomy of Solanum sections Dunaliana and Irenosolanum (Solanaceae). Doctoral dissertation presented to the City University of New York, NY." year="2012">McClelland 2012</bibRefCitation>
), the inflorescence of this species emerges from the middle of the internode. 
<taxonomicName id="B180709B4546A297C8DD46939F3F52D4" authorityName="D. McClelland" authorityYear="2020" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Solanum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Solanum labyrinthinum" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="labyrinthinum">
<emphasis id="CE273D64777490D1DE44C5CD6CC803CF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Solanum labyrinthinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="C79C78CBED206538E68599BE0E86B73B" genus="S." lsidName="S. peekelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="peekelii">
<emphasis id="DD36E9782C382AEA5205865901C7A6A7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. peekelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with which it has been confused (see below) in its narrow completely glabrous leaves at maturity with distinctive appressed stellate trichomes when young, its fewer principal leaf veins (7-10 versus 10-14) that often dry yellowish, its slightly smaller flowers (ca. 1.2 cm in diameter versus to 1.5 cm in diameter) and fruits, and in its distribution. The stems of 
<taxonomicName id="C5A297E864925B52D2B0DBA0857C5562" genus="S." lsidName="S. labyrinthinum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="labyrinthinum">
<emphasis id="F2537E3CD62F282F2DE8CB9D839457BA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. labyrinthinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are often purplish tinged, and the flowers are darker purple than those of 
<taxonomicName id="BEF71FB210FCC183F2734E628208030A" genus="S." lsidName="S. peekelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="peekelii">
<emphasis id="30ED7BFB67BB48884C4AD42203B05A08" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. peekelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C982B9AB6E314161244822F9D6B9DBDD" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<bibRefCitation id="D9ED527EF726C0CF7EC6BE3DD027700A" author="Symon, DE" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the Adelaide Botanic Gardens" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="1 - 171" refId="B25" refString="Symon, DE, 1985. The Solanaceae of New Guinea. Journal of the Adelaide Botanic Gardens 8: 1 - 171" title="The Solanaceae of New Guinea." volume="8" year="1985">Symon (1985)</bibRefCitation>
applied the name 
<taxonomicName id="B48DD63C0B9FEC445AE9DF4F016D1961" genus="S." lsidName="S. peekelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="peekelii">
<emphasis id="6C273130ED8FE16BB7C1A3AEB5265D29" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. peekelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to the plants we here recognise as 
<taxonomicName id="E8C5DD0C0B7F7A20D7972E0562588E5A" genus="S." lsidName="S. labyrinthinum" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="labyrinthinum">
<emphasis id="23D91E45F06A6127394C7150ABAC84CD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. labyrinthinum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, then applied the name 
<taxonomicName id="367269BD62C3A29F261527FD792A19B3" genus="S." lsidName="S. torricellense" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="torricellense">
<emphasis id="38415B760E494C8704AA51F2B14415E5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. torricellense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to plants matching the description of 
<taxonomicName id="930D3D90B48729FC09F19D880F144233" genus="S." lsidName="S. peekelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="peekelii">
<emphasis id="65875478EF97FEADB4172841FA1EBEFF" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. peekelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and provided a new name for plants matching the type of 
<taxonomicName id="C22EC438F4649E7FB7DF43B845005BAD" genus="S." lsidName="S. torricellense" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="torricellense">
<emphasis id="5EF8BAF182AB4A4358AEA17CBF129749" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. torricellense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, thus creating a taxonomic labyrinth (see below under typification of 
<taxonomicName id="241E33FFD4552DB8BB6B6D29BD9A35E0" genus="S." lsidName="S. peekelii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="peekelii">
<emphasis id="E556B35A576D097263DE0704715D742C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">S. peekelii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for details, and 
<taxonomicName id="6E2BBEF273F632E131DA9CE1F76213E5" family="Solanaceae" genus="S." lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="family">Solanaceae</taxonomicName>
Source (www.solanaceaesource.org) for descriptions of the other taxa involved).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
